title: OneWeb Completes V1 Constellation With India Launch
summary: The ISRO successfully launched 26 OneWeb internet satellites, completing OneWeb's first generation constellation.

title: Space Force selects 18 vendors to provide space data analytics and software services
summary: The Space Systems Command announced March 24 it has selected 18 vendors to provide data analytics and software services to help decision makers analyze information about the space domain.

title: Canada agrees to ISS extension to 2030
summary: The Canadian government formally committed March 24 to an extension of the International Space Station to 2030, joining other Western partners but not Russia.

title: OneWeb completes initial constellation with launch from India
summary: OneWeb has finished its initial satellite constellation buildout, as India and its space agency, the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO), made its second orbital flight of 2023 by flying 36 of the company’s satellites aboard its LVM3 (previously known as the GSLV Mk III) launch vehicle from the Satish Dhawan Space Centre.

title: Dawn Aerospace's Spaceplane Gets Green Light for Suborbital Test Flights in New Zealand
summary: New Zealand-based aerospace company, Dawn Aerospace, has received certification from the New Zealand Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) for its Mk-II Aurora spaceplane's rocket-powered flight campaign. The Mk-II Aurora's mission is to fly twice to space in a day, demonstrating that rocket-powered systems can be as reusable as commercial aircraft.
